    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-12-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="282"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <head>282. Memorandum for the Record<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d282fn0"
                        >Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_INR1">INR</gloss>/IL
                        Historical Files, S.G. 22, December 14, 1961. Secret; Eyes Only. Prepared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_PTA1">Parrott</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-12-08">December 8, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Minutes of Special Group Meeting, 8 December 1961</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PRESENT</head>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_TMD1">General Taylor</persName>, Mr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName>, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GRL1"
                            >Gilpatric</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_CGCP1">General
                            Cabell</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LEG1">General Lansdale</persName> attended for items 1
                        and 2</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Here follows discussion unrelated to Cuba.]</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">2. Cuba</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LEG1">General Lansdale</persName> presented the outline of
                    a program<note n="1" xml:id="d282fn1">See <ref target="#d281">Document
                        281</ref>.</note> designed to overthrow the <persName corresp="#p_CRF1"
                        >Castro</persName> government. This program is centered around the selection
                    and eventual introduction into Cuba of a nucleus of anti-<persName
                        corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> Cubans; once they are in the country and
                    in a position to operate, then a number of collateral supporting actions would
                    be undertaken.</p>
                <p>It was agreed that the immediate requirement was for the selection of a suitable
                    group which could agree on a platform for an eventual new government, and which
                    is willing and capable of carrying out the proposed tasks inside the country.
                    When a selection has been made the program will be discussed further with higher
                    authority.</p>
                <pb facs="0728" n="696" xml:id="pg_696"/>
                <p>It was noted that <persName corresp="#p_LEG1">General Lansdale</persName> would
                    report periodically to the Special Group on progress he is making.</p>
                <p>[Here follows discussion unrelated to Cuba.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Thomas A. Parrott</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d282fn2">Printed from a copy that indicates <persName
                                corresp="#p_PTA1">Parrott</persName> signed the original.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
